  <section id="advancedSettings">
    <title>Advanced settings</title>
    <p>When you click the "Advanced settings" button, a window will appear giving you even further configuration options.</p>
    <terms>
      <title>Interface</title>
      <item>
        <title>Hide album art</title>
        <p>This will hide the album art in the "Now Playing" browser and the notification popup.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <title>Hide favorite icon</title>
        <p>This will hide the favorite icon in the player.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <title>Use backdrops (restart required)</title>
        <p>This will put the artists image in a darkend version behind the contents of the "Now Playing" browser.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <title>Use legacy tray icon</title>
        <p>This option is only available if you compiled GMPC with AppIndicator support. This option allows you to seamlessly switch between the AppIndicator and the old tray icon. More information on this is available in the "Preferences"-&gt;"Notification" section.</p>
      </item>
    </terms>
    <terms>
      <title>Browsers</title>
      <item>
        <title/>
        <p>These items allow you to individually select, which of GMPC's internal browsers should be visible.</p>
      </item>
    </terms>
  </section>
